<HEAD>Reporter Who Broke Hart Story Sleeps in Suite Former Candidate Used</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORGANTOWN, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A reporter who helped break the story
that dashed Gary Hart's presidential hopes has found that just like
politics, the lecture circuit makes strange bedfellows.
   ``I never would have guessed that I would sleep in the same bed
that Gary Hart slept in,'' Jim McGee told an audience at West
Virginia University's Mountainlair student union Tuesday.
   The school invited the former Miami Herald reporter to speak.
Afterward, McGee was lodged in the same university suite where Hart
stayed when he spoke at the school in 1987, shortly after news of
his relationship with model Donna Rice forced him to drop out of
the presidential race.
   McGee helped stake out Hart's Washington townhouse after the
former Colorado senator denied rumors he was having an extramarital
affair.
   ``For us, it was always a story about telling the truth. It
didn't start out as a story about private lives or sex lives or
anything like that,'' said McGee, who now works for The Washington
Post.
