<HEAD>Ex-Husband Of John Wayne's Daughter Arrested In Her Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A surgeon was arrested in
connection with an attack on his ex-wife, Aissa Wayne, the daughter
of the late John Wayne, police said today.
   Thomas A. Gionis, 35, of Pomona was arrested late Tuesday night
in the Oct. 3, 1988, attack on Ms. Wayne and her then-boyfriend,
Roger Luby, police Sgt. Trent Harris said.
   Gionis, who was jailed without bail for investigation of
conspiracy to commit assault with a deadly weapon, was the third
person arrested in the attack at Luby's Newport Beach estate.
   Police in March arrested two employees of a Los Angeles private
detective firm retained by Gionis in a dispute in which Ms. Wayne
is trying to gain custody of their now 2-year-old daughter,
Anastasia. A judge in January granted custody to Gionis.
   An arrest warrant also has been issued for the firm's owner, O.
Daniel Gal, who authorities believe fled to Europe after
questioning.
