mother, Pilar Wayne, said Gionis' arrest was ``marvelous.''
   ``I'm speechless. Oh my God, I'm absolutely speechless. This
thing has kept me up night after night after night worrying about
it. I didn't expect anything like this,'' Mrs. Wayne said.
   Ms. Wayne, 32, was bloodied in an attack by two men, while Luby,
52, was beaten and had his Achilles tendon slashed. As the men
left, one of them said, ``You're messing with the wrong guy. Next
time, we kill you,'' police have said.
   The couple separated in 1987 after one year of marriage, and
their divorce became final last year.
