<HEAD>Senegal's Independence Day Marked by Protest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAKAR, Senegal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police used tear gas and arrested
protesters in a disturbance that broke out after independence day
celebrations, witnesses said Wednesday.
   Demonstrators stormed a poor residential area of Dakar following
Tuesday's parade marking the 29th anniversary of Senegal's
independence from France. They threw stones, set fire to tires,
pulled down utility poles and tried to erect street barricades,
witnesses said.
   Police broke up the protest using tear gas, they said. Several
dozen protesters were arrested and charged with vandalism, police
said.
