<HEAD>Head of Ethics Office Nominated to Veterans Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush has nominated Frank Nebeker,
head of the Office of Government Ethics, to a 15-year term as chief
judge of the U.S. Court of Veterans Appeals.
   The White House said the post that Nebeker was chosen to fill is
a new position.
   Nebeker, a 58-year-old native of Salt Lake City, Utah, has
headed the ethics office since early last year. Before that he was
an associate judge on the District of Columbia Court of Appeals
from 1969-87. He was chief of the appellate division of the U.S.
Court of Appeals of the District of Columbia and the District of
Columbia Court of Appeals from 1962-69.
   He also has been an adjunct professor at the American University
Law School. Nebeker graduated from Weber College and the University
of Utah and got his law degree from American University in 1955.
   No replacement was named at the ethics office.
