<FIRST>u i BC-Poland-Text     04-05 0213</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Poland-Text,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Text of Final `Round Table' Communique</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Poland Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of a communique agreed
upon by Solidarity leader Lech Walesa and Gen. Czeslaw Kiszczak,
the Polish interior minister, at the final session of ``round
table'' discussions Wednesday night, as read on state radio and
translated by The Associated Press:
   The participants of the plenary session of the round table on
April 5, 1989, accept the decisions adopted in the course of the
talks of the groups and subgroups of the working teams, and express
the will for joint actions in order to implement them.
   The sides participating in the session decide to establish an
Arbitration Commission that will consist of representatives of the
forces present at the round table.
   The tasks of the Arbitration Commission would include the
assessment of the realization of the resolutions of the round
table, common search for solutions in other matters which the sides
consider significant, and fulfilling a mediation function in
situations of conflict.
   The participants of the round table express deep respect and
appreciation for the effort and work of all people taking part in
the process of the round table.
   The participants of the round table consider the mission of the
round table as completed.
</TEXT>
