cars, the price of gasoline may not be a big
worry.
   Inside the Fleetwood Sedan, there were pleasant surprisestouches. Lighted
vanity mirrors popped out of the ceiling for
rear-seat passengers. Front-seat occupants had thn the back of the sun
visors. Floor mats were reversible
and machine washable _ the short nap on one side was for sloppy
winter weather, with  the other side ideal for
