<FIRST>r f BC-AutoSales-Table     04-05 0590</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Sales-Table,0666</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Auto Sales</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are sales results for the eight major U.S.
automakers for the third period of March 1989.
   Percentage changes in sales are based on average daily sales
during each period rather than comparisons of straight totals.
There were 10 selling days in the period this year and 10 selling
days last year.
   For the month, there were 27 selling days this year and 27
selling days last year, and for the year so far, 76 selling days
this year and 77 selling days last year.
   Cars and trucks made in the United States by Honda, Nissan,
Toyota, Mazda and Mitsubishi are counted as domestic and appear in
this table.
   Cars and trucks imported for sale under the GM, Ford and
Chrysler names are counted as foreign. Some foreign automakers said
they would not report March sales figures until Wednesday.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>DOMESTIC CAR TOTAL</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   March 21-31: 272,520 vs. 332,721, down 18.1 percent.
   Month: 639,631 vs. 734,614, down 12.9 percent.
   Year: 1,702,240 vs. 1,914,022, down 9.9 percent.
