<SECOND>AM-Gerber President,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>Carnation Senior Vice President Named President At Gerber</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREMONT, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gerber Products Co., the world's largest
baby-food maker, said Wednesday that Alfred A. Piergallini, a
senior vice president at Carnation Co., will become its president
and chief operating officer.
   ``I expect him to provide strong operating leadership to our
growing Gerber business and also to serve as my long-range backup
to ensure continuity of Gerber management during the next decade
and beyond,'' said David W. Johnson, Gerber's board chairman and
chief executive officer.
   Johnson, 57, had held the title of president. Gerber had no
chief operating officer. The appointment is effective April 17.
   Piergallini, 42, began his business career as a marketing
trainee at Procter &amp; Gamble Co. in 1970.
   In 1976, he joined Beverage Management Inc. as marketing
planning manager, and in 1979 he joined Sara Lee Corp. as vice
president and general manager of the midwest region for Shasta
Beverages.
   He joined Carnation in 1986 as vice president and general
manager of the Friskies Pet Care division, and was promoted to
senior vice president in 1987.
   Gerber reported earnings of $21.2 million on sales of $943
million for its fiscal year ended March 31, 1988.
